and outdoor adventures in this scenic region.","heroImage":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1565039320828-e97535b882e0?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxMZWt2YXR0bmV0JTIwbGFrZSUyMFN3ZWRlbnxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzNDMzMDg5fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Anatoliy Gromov"},"cardImage":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1565039320828-e97535b882e0?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxMZWt2YXR0bmV0JTIwbGFrZSUyMFN3ZWRlbnxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzNDMzMDg5fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080"},{"id":"gotland","name":"Gotland","nameIt":"Gotland","capital":"Visby","lat":57.64,"lng":18.43,"emoji":"🏝️","colour":"ff2196f3","boundingBox":{"north":58,"south":56.9,"east":19.3,"west":17.8},"placeCount":12,"restaurantCount":14,"bestTimeToVisit":"Best from May to September for beach weather, sea activities, and the island's medieval charm.","heroImage":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1510256506868-484d0db06ee2?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxMdW1tZWx1bmRhJTIwQ2F2ZSUyMHN0YWxhY3RpdGVzfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM0MzM4OTB8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Joshua Sortino"},"cardImage":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1510256506868-484d0db06ee2?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxMdW1tZWx1bmRhJTIwQ2F2ZSUyMHN0YWxhY3RpdGVzfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM0MzM4OTB8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080"}],"top10":[{"rank":1,"name":"Stockholm","placeId":"stockholm","regionId":"central_sweden","regionName":"Central Sweden","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1590496913937-939a9b0680bd?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxTdG9ja2hvbG0lMjBHYW1sYSUyMFN0YW4lMjBPbGQlMjBUb3dufGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM0MjY2ODJ8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Aron Fornasiero"},"description":"Sweden's capital and largest city, built across 14 islands with stunning archipelago views and a charming medieval Old Town (Gamla Stan). It offers world-class museums like the Vasa Museum, vibrant neighborhoods, and excellent restaurants showcasing Nordic cuisine."},{"rank":2,"name":"Gothenburg","placeId":"gothenburg","regionId":"west_coast","regionName":"West Coast","image":null,"description":"Sweden's second-largest city and the gateway to the West Coast, known for its charming canals, vibrant food scene, and maritime heritage. It offers excellent museums, shopping, restaurants, and serves as a perfect base for exploring the region."},{"rank":3,"name":"Malmö","placeId":"malmo","regionId":"southern_sweden","regionName":"Southern Sweden","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1689259377284-0030ca5895f1?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxUdXJuaW5nJTIwVG9yc28lMjBNYWxtJUMzJUI2fGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM0MjM4MDR8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Boris Hadjur"},"description":"Sweden's third-largest city and gateway to the south, famous for its striking Turning Torso skyscraper and vibrant cultural scene. It offers excellent museums, restaurants, and a lively waterfront atmosphere with easy access to Copenhagen across the Öresund Bridge."},{"rank":4,"name":"Vasa Museum","placeId":"vasa_museum","regionId":"stockholm","regionName":"Stockholm","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1637682398896-0797c2b78354?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxWYXNhJTIwTXVzZXVtJTIwc2hpcCUyMFN0b2NraG9sbXxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzNDIzNjkwfDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Kylli Kittus"},"description":"Home to the remarkably preserved warship Vasa that sank in 1628 and was salvaged in 1961, making it the only intact 17th-century warship in the world. The museum tells the fascinating story of Swedish naval history and maritime culture through this stunning vessel and extensive exhibits."},{"rank":5,"name":"Drottningholm Palace","placeId":"drottningholm_palace","regionId":"uppsala_gavleborg","regionName":"Uppsala and Gävleborg","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1719882610628-c946ee87cd8f?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxEcm90dG5pbmdob2xtJTIwUGFsYWNlJTIwU3dlZGVuJTIwcm95YWx8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzQyMzc0N3ww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Andriy Oliynyk"},"description":"Sweden's royal residence and one of Europe's finest palaces, located on an island west of Stockholm in the Uppsala region, featuring exquisite baroque architecture and beautifully manicured gardens. The palace is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and offers guided tours showcasing royal Swedish history and magnificent interior design."},{"rank":6,"name":"Skansen","placeId":"skansen","regionId":"stockholm","regionName":"Stockholm","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1688938934253-360b44752d2a?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxTa2Fuc2VuJTIwU3RvY2tob2xtJTIwb3Blbi1haXIlMjBtdXNldW18ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzQyMzY5NHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Amelia Ailema"},"description":"An open-air museum on Djurgården island showcasing Swedish culture, traditional buildings, and Nordic wildlife in their natural habitats. It's a perfect blend of history and nature where visitors can experience traditional crafts, local food, and encounter elk, bears, and other Scandinavian animals."},{"rank":7,"name":"Uppsala Cathedral","placeId":"uppsala_cathedral","regionId":"uppsala_gavleborg","regionName":"Uppsala and Gävleborg","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1595537814477-ce4e9d1d4e80?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxVcHBzYWxhJTIwQ2F0aGVkcmFsJTIwU3dlZGVufGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODQwMjYzNTF8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Yang Yang"},"description":"Sweden's largest and tallest cathedral, located in the historic university city of Uppsala about an hour north of Stockholm. The Gothic masterpiece is one of Scandinavia's most important religious and architectural landmarks, attracting history and architecture enthusiasts worldwide."},{"rank":8,"name":"Stockholm Archipelago","placeId":"stockholm_archipelago","regionId":"central_sweden","regionName":"Central Sweden","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1508738102835-f1fe48178e7b?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxTdG9ja2hvbG0lMjBhcmNoaXBlbGFnbyUyMGlzbGFuZHN8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzQyNjY4Nnww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Max Hermansson"},"description":"A stunning natural wonder comprising thousands of islands and skerries stretching eastward from Stockholm into the Baltic Sea. Perfect for boat tours, kayaking, swimming, and experiencing pristine Scandinavian coastal beauty with charming island communities."},{"rank":9,"name":"Visby","placeId":"visby","regionId":"east_coast","regionName":"East Coast","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1632495896324-0cf8adcea7cc?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxWaXNieSUyMG1lZGlldmFsJTIwY2l0eSUyMHdhbGxzJTIwR290bGFuZHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzNDI2NjI3fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Oleh Holodyshyn"},"description":"A medieval walled city on the island of Gotland with remarkably preserved 13th-century city walls and narrow cobblestone streets filled with historic buildings and ruins. A UNESCO World Heritage site essential for experiencing medieval Scandinavia and enjoying the Gotland island experience."},{"rank":10,"name":"Abisko National Park","placeId":"abisko_national_park","regionId":"norrbotten","regionName":"Norrbotten","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1665189196532-cf3575e44ad9?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxBYmlza28lMjBOYXRpb25hbCUyMFBhcmslMjBoaWtpbmclMjB0cmFpbHN8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzQzMDM4OHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Elle Leontiev"},"description":"A pristine subarctic wilderness reserve featuring dramatic mountain landscapes, pristine forests, and the famous turquoise Abisko Lake, with excellent hiking trails for all seasons. The park is a biodiversity hotspot and offers some of Sweden's most accessible yet untouched Arctic nature experiences."}]}